id: pm-ixi1
title: Stop listing provided --flag as missing in error recovery bundle
description: "When a flag was provided but its value rejected (e.g. malformed --reminder value), the recovery bundle reported the flag as 'missing: --reminder' and 'suggested_retry' was an identical command. Now filter inferredMissing to exclude flags that were already provided."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,errors,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-16T21:54:12.960Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T23:45:07.023Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: Recovery bundle for malformed --reminder no longer claims --reminder is missing; suggested_retry only repeats the original command if no other recovery hint exists.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Fixed recovery payload generation so already-provided malformed flags are not listed as missing and identical retry commands are omitted.
expected_result: Malformed --reminder recovery shows provided_fields but no missing --reminder and no no-op suggested_retry.
actual_result: "Focused regression, dogfood, and full release gate passed with the expected recovery envelope."
